b'Employment Click here to apply for a job \xc2\xbbWhen you click above you will be directed to the University of Illinois statewide web site, which serves Rockford, as well as Chicago, Springfield and Urbana. If you need assistance with applying online, please call the help desk at (312) 413-4848.Thank you for your interest in becoming a part of the University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford team where our mission is to educate, innovate and serve. Our team includes physicians, administrators, researchers, nurses, administrative support, medical business office staff, maintenance workers, medical assistants and others, all committed to providing exceptional education for our students, an environment where research flourishes and excellent medical care for our patients.Employment TypesFaculty: employees that teach medical, pharmacy, nursing, public health, and/or medical biotechnology studentsCivil Service: employees that provide services such as nursing, administrative support, laboratory, maintenance, accounting and billing/codingExtra Help: temporary Civil Service employeesStandardized Patients:\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0a person trained to portray the role of a patient, thereby allowing medical students to practice physical exams, history taking and communication skills in the medical field. This experience gives students an opportunity to learn and to be evaluated on learned skills in a simulated clinical environment.Application ProcessFaculty:Follow application link on online postingCivil Service:\xc2\xa0Apply online at jobs.uic.edu; questions should be referred to UIC Help Desk at (312) 413-4848. Human Resources will review your qualifications and, if qualified, contact you to schedule an examination.\xc2\xa0Civil Service exams are administered on Tuesday mornings or Thursday afternoons.* Please note that your qualifications for Civil Service examinations are determined based on application materials.\xc2\xa0Applications containing employment information from your first job through your current position, a detailed resume, copy of your college/university transcripts, and DD214, if applicable, must be received in Human Resources by the closing date of the job.\xc2\xa0Incomplete applications will not be considered.\xc2\xa0After the application deadline, the names of the top three candidates will be referred to the department for interviews.Extra Help:\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0Apply online at jobs.uic.edu; questions should be referred to UIC Help Desk at (312) 413-4848. E-mail rockfordhr@uic.edu to express interest in a particular extra help job.Standardized Patients:\xc2\xa0The Office of Medical Education and Evaluation at the College of Medicine Rockford hires Extra Help employees who work with medical students to complete clinical skills assessments. We are recruiting individuals who can communicate effectively and be available for varied daytime hours to be Standardized Patients. For more information and to ensure your application is directed appropriately, contact the office at seemac@uic.edu.Standardized Patient Job DescriptionCurrent VacanciesFor a listing of current Rockford vacancies\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0click here.\xc2\xa0'
b'Employment'
b'Click here to apply for a job \xc2\xbb'
b'Click here to apply for a job \xc2\xbb'
b'When you click above you will be directed to the University of Illinois statewide web site, which serves Rockford, as well as Chicago, Springfield and Urbana. If you need assistance with applying online, please call the help desk at (312) 413-4848.'
b'Thank you for your interest in becoming a part of the University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford team where our mission is to educate, innovate and serve. Our team includes physicians, administrators, researchers, nurses, administrative support, medical business office staff, maintenance workers, medical assistants and others, all committed to providing exceptional education for our students, an environment where research flourishes and excellent medical care for our patients.'
b'Employment Types'
b'Faculty: employees that teach medical, pharmacy, nursing, public health, and/or medical biotechnology students'
b'Civil Service: employees that provide services such as nursing, administrative support, laboratory, maintenance, accounting and billing/coding'
b'Extra Help: temporary Civil Service employees'
b'Standardized Patients:\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0a person trained to portray the role of a patient, thereby allowing medical students to practice physical exams, history taking and communication skills in the medical field. This experience gives students an opportunity to learn and to be evaluated on learned skills in a simulated clinical environment.'
b'Application Process'
b'Faculty:'
b'Follow application link on online posting'
b'Civil Service:\xc2\xa0'
b'Apply online at jobs.uic.edu; questions should be referred to UIC Help Desk at (312) 413-4848. Human Resources will review your qualifications and, if qualified, contact you to schedule an examination.\xc2\xa0Civil Service exams are administered on Tuesday mornings or Thursday afternoons.'
b'jobs.uic.edu'
b'* Please note that your qualifications for Civil Service examinations are determined based on application materials.\xc2\xa0Applications containing employment information from your first job through your current position, a detailed resume, copy of your college/university transcripts, and DD214, if applicable, must be received in Human Resources by the closing date of the job.\xc2\xa0Incomplete applications will not be considered.\xc2\xa0After the application deadline, the names of the top three candidates will be referred to the department for interviews.'
b'Extra Help:\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0\xc2\xa0'
b'Apply online at jobs.uic.edu; questions should be referred to UIC Help Desk at (312) 413-4848. E-mail rockfordhr@uic.edu to express interest in a particular extra help job.'
b'jobs.uic.edu'
b'rockfordhr@uic.edu'
b'Standardized Patients:\xc2\xa0'
b'The Office of Medical Education and Evaluation at the College of Medicine Rockford hires Extra Help employees who work with medical students to complete clinical skills assessments. We are recruiting individuals who can communicate effectively and be available for varied daytime hours to be Standardized Patients. For more information and to ensure your application is directed appropriately, contact the office at seemac@uic.edu.'
b'seemac@uic.edu'
